The @cite{OpenSS7} @value{PACKAGE_TITLE} package is a @dfn{STREAMS} framework for @cite{Linux} that
is compatible with @cite{SVR 4.2 MP} @dfn{STREAMS}.

@cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} is intendeed as a high-performance, production replacement for the
buggy and deprecated @cite{Linux STREAMS (LiS)}.  In contrast, @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} has the
following features in contrast to @cite{Linux STREAMS}:

@multitable @columnfractions .50 .50
@item @b{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}}
@tab @b{Linux STREAMS (LiS)}
@item
Provided and optimized for Linux.  Ports to other OSs (BSD?) possible.
@tab
Maintain portability across Linux, User Space, QNX, DOS and other ports.
@item
Promotes mainstream kernel adoption.
@tab
Places portability concerns before mainstream kernel adoption.
@item
Lindented and follows normal kernel formatting and coding practices.
@tab
Non-lindented, does not follow normal kernel formatting and coding practice.
@item
Provides compatibility modes for AIX, HPUX, OSF, Solaris, UnixWare, SVR 4.2 and LiS.  Supports all
majjor SVR 4.2 variants.
@tab
Provides some compatibility interfaces but also many Linux-derived inetrfaces specific to LiS.
@item
Licensed under GPL with commercial licensing avaliable.
@tab
Dubiously licensed under LGPL.
@item
Supports full SVR4.2 MP sychronization models.
@tab
Supports only a single, Linux derived synchronization model.
@item
Runs at SoftIRQ.
@tab
Separate kernel threads.
@item
Provides common SVR4.2 system tunable parameters as sysctls as well as /proc filesystem support for
debugging.
@tab
Provides only log based debugging.
@item
Provides support for SVR4.2 STREAMS and other utilities.
@tab
Provides a limited set of LiS only Linux-derived utlities.
@item
Provides full named-streams device and device filesystem support.
@tab
Provides only character-based node support.
@end multitable

